### Project Overview: Real-Time Voice-to-Text Desktop Application

**Description:**  
This project is a cross-platform desktop application that converts speech from a microphone into text in real-time and simulates keyboard input at the cursor's location. It supports multiple transcription methods, including OpenAI-compatible API endpoints (with custom server URLs) and locally downloaded Whisper models for offline use.

**Key Features:**
- Real-time speech-to-text conversion.
- Simulates keyboard input at the cursor position.
- Cross-platform compatibility (Windows, macOS, Linux).
- Supports both cloud-based (OpenAI-compatible APIs) and local (Whisper models) transcription.
- Customizable API endpoints for flexibility.
- Offline functionality with locally hosted Whisper models.

**Target Audience:**  
Developers, productivity enthusiasts, and users seeking accessible text input solutions.